    >During this selective two-year research master, I learned all aspects of number crunching: the foundations of statistics, applied programming skills, and zoned in on a variety of  techniques, such as Bayesian statistics, Causal Inference and Multilevel Modelling. I am currently specializing in machine learning and front-end development! I am also working on my thesis, in which I model ordinal estimates of quantitative measures in time-dependent processes.
