      subtitle="2023 to now at Utrecht University, Utrecht, The Netherlands"
    >
      ASReview is a system that uses machine learning to help select relevant papers for literature reviews. I am currently comparing various ways of calculating inter-rater reliability. Several raters can rate scientific papers as either relevant or irrelevant. I look to which degree these different raters coincide, and how we can calculate this degree in the best way.
    </TimeLineElement>
